values: Hey, I forgot about this thing!

I spent Thanksgiving in Colorado Springs! The reason for my visit was to see a good friend of mine. The trip was nice but also stressful. I tried to enjoy the best of it. Selah was with me and it was hard to keep her content. I did not take many of her toys so I had to keep her occupied during the early and mid afternoon hours. Most of the days we headed out to places by 4 o'clock. The sun sets faster over there so once the light was gone, activities were limited. So was my photography. Truth be known, I was not able to photograph as much. It was hard to juggle a baby and a bulky camera. I did photograph the snow!

The best parts of the trip was the answers to my prayers! On my way there, I was worried about Selah's ears during the flight. I heard stories about how babies get fussy and cry during departure and especially arrivals. The pressure changes effect us all but how do babies handle it? I prayed that she would be okay and even coming down she was smiling at herself in the bathroom mirror after a diaper change. Upon returning to Houston, I prayed that she would fall into a deep sleep the entire flight. I could not reach her bottles and diapers in case she got fussy and needed those things. I was sitting next to a tall business man that it would have been tedious to get out to the aisle while carrying Selah. I hoped and prayed, "God just put her in a deep sleep." I thought that would be highly unlikely but nevertheless I did some wishful thinking. Well as it turned out, Selah slept through the entire flight! Even when everyone got off the plane, she was still asleep on my lap! I had to wake her up to get up from the seats and get moving! It was so convenient and awesome! I was so glad to be home!!!

When the righteous are in authority, the people rejoice;
      But when a wicked man rules, the people groan.

Sen. Obama is fully pro-choice:

Roe V Wade
Supports

Co-sponsor of the "Freedom of Choice Act"*
"I have consistently advocated for reproductive choice and will make preserving women's rights under Roe v. Wade a priority as President."

*Note: The "Freedom of Choice Act" is a bill that would invalidate virtually all state and federal limitations on abortion, including partial-birth abortion.

Partial Birth Abortion Ban
Opposes

The partial-birth abortion procedure, a surgical abortion that is typically performed during the third trimester or later part of the second trimester of pregnancy, involves pulling a living baby feet-first out of the womb, except for the head, puncturing the skull and suctioning out the brain. The great majority of partial-birth abortions are preformed on healthy babies of healthy mothers.

"I am extremely concerned that [Gonzales v. Carhart*] will embolden state legislatures to enact further measures to restrict a woman's right to choose, and that the conservative Supreme Court justices will look for other opportunities to erode Roe v. Wade."

*Note: Gonzales v. Carhart is the April 2007 Supreme Court decision upholding the constitutionality of the federal Partial-Birth Abortion Act.

Taxpayer Funding of Abortion
Supports

As recently as April 2005, Obama voted against an amendment in the Senate to prevent taxpayer funding of groups that promote or perform abortions in other nations.

His campaign has stated that he "does not support" the Hyde Amendment, which prohibits taxpayer funding of abortion through the Medicaid program.

Parental Notification Law
Opposes

Voted to block a bill that would have required an abortionist to notify at least one parent before performing an abortion on a minor girl from another state.

Protecting Abortion Survivors
Opposes

In 2000, the Born-Alive Infants Protection Act (BAIPA) was first introduced in Congress. This was a two-paragraph bill intended to clarify that any baby who is entirely expelled from his or her mother, and who shows any signs of life, is to be regarded as a legal "person" for all federal law purposes, whether or not the baby was born during an attempted abortion.

Voted three times against a bill in the Illinois State Senate that would have provided protection for babies who survive abortions equal to protection received by babies who are spontaneously born prematurely.

Where do the candidates stand on KEY ISSUES? Find out before you cast your vote.

You won't have my vote! I'm so furious that anyone would even support this massacre of the unborn! When I learned about what Planned Parenthood was doing, I was disgusted! Barack and many others often talk about protecting women's rights but who will defend the unborn? Yes, there are actually some babies that survive and are born alive after failed abortions! Sometimes they are discarded and left to die! How quickly we forget how small and fragile we once were. All that was needed for all of us to grow was time and our mother's wombs. Yes, life begins at conception!
I don't have any updates but Selah says hello! It's not easy photographing her. She gets so serious when she sees the camera! She looks away more often than not. She'll have to get use to the lens.
Worry about nothing, pray about everything. Put on a heart of rejoicing! Proverbs 17:22 "A joyful heart causes good healing." and 15:15 "A cheerful heart has a continual feast."

Hi gals! My husband is a spender! I don't get to shop much because of it. But this week, I made a purchase. A purse was on my "get list" for about a year now. Maybe longer. Urban Outfitters had one that fit my budget so its on route to me, God willing. I think its cute but mostly practical.

I returned to work today! I'm not excited about it. It's just a new routine from all the days I've had last month. Taking care of babies, newborns to be exact, is not easy. I guess it depends on the baby but mine was very fussy the first weeks. She had colic. I think she has calmed some but it is still challenging to keep her content. After delivering, I experienced some really low drops emotionally. I don't care to relive those days. I'm better now! Before returning to work I spent the last two days with my gorgeous husband. I helped him with his route for the new job he recently took. He is in charge of putting out products in the aisle at the grocery stores (Randalls). Well it is a lot of work. I never knew how much work it was to manage the grocery stores! The shelves are so crowded! And how many brands of soy sauce do you really need? Anyway, the last two days were awesome despite the work. He won't have this job forever though. Company/Randalls contract expired so they are letting people go. It's okay; he'll find a better job very soon! I love my husband! He is so considerate and available! He's also delicious to look at. Everyday I get to look into his blue eyes. He takes care of me and Selah. Most importantly he is a man of God. His foundation for living is the Word of God and that is priceless.

Well I was not happy with the results from our maternity session this weekend. Nonetheless, I did approve of these. Saturday the weather was beautiful! It felt like summer except not as hot. I was reminded of Puerto Vallarta. The day was spent with hubby and it felt like a vacation! We ate lunch at Harry's, photographed, went to see butterflies at the Museum of Natural Science and then ate an afternoon snack at La Tapatia. He had the day off from work for my birthday! God blessed me with simple joy and surprises. This birthday was REALLY different than all the rest.

No, my bad, according to the OBGYN yesterday, my due date is 03/21/08! So much sooner than I thought! I am not sure when I conceived to begin with so I don't know exactly. Selah come in God's perfect timing. I pray, in Jesus' Name. Amen.

Hi "Y'ALL". I haven't posted much on LJ or anywhere else. I've been busy. My belly is much bigger now. It's hard to sleep and challenging to walk. My skin itches a lot. I'm often thirsty. Selah moves inside of me too. She hiccups. How awesome to know that there is a growing life inside me! It's a miracle. I just don't understand how people can take that lightly. She is due anytime now, March 28. Fear begins to set in sometimes but I choose not to hold on to it. I know this experience is going to be all new to me. I know I can't deliver a baby in my own strength. I need God's supernatural power, help and guidance. I need HIM. I know He will get me through it. Whatever comes, he always gets me through it. Thank you Jesus! We already have the crib, stroller, car seat and baby clothes. All gifts received from my baby shower! God so provided for baby. I'm humbled and my faith in Him has increased as I know that he takes care of those that wait upon and trust in him. God is so GOOD! We even have money for the time when I will be out of work; 4 weeks. I came into this new stage with nothing and now I have what I need for baby!!! It wasn't even my doing. I prayed and God has given what I need to get started! He fills me with peace that surpasses any human understanding. It's the only way I can explain it. My life is in his hands and I know that whatever happens, he is in control! That's a really cool feeling.

On another note, people have been telling me that I look like I'm carrying a boy. Ahhh!!! It's hard to imagine a boy in the crib and around the house! Well whatever God does, it will be perfect! I want a girl! Hehe.

I got stretchmarks! I put Tummy Honey and Zinc Oxide on my belly often to repair skin and keep it moist. Too bad. I hope they go away.

Saturday photo session; windy and COLD! We started VERY early. This is Lydia. Photographing people is challenging and inspiring for me. I was uncertain and reluctant at first but after a few shots I was able to warm up and focus. We did a lot of walking which was good for me. It was fun! I was tired after.

Hi LJ friends! I was passing through...I commented on some of you. I'm at work. I returned today after a week of paid time off! Praise God! I was away to Puerto Vallarta. It's okay out there but after a week you begin to miss home church. It was honeymoon time! It's true, I'm married. I've been single for a very long time; it was just me and God; us and God, hehe. It was great! But...God brought a beautiful man into my life. I am now Mrs. Brent Peddy! I know it may take awhile to get use to the name...Medina is one I was so ready to give up. Anyway, here's a brief photo...just for fun. This is my gorgeous honey brought to me from God! Cheese! I don't look so hot... "Come and see what God has done, how awesome his works in man's behalf!" Psalm 66:5 "Taste and see that the LORD is good; blessed is the man who takes refuge in him." Psalm 34:8
